[The midges that cause EHD, and the vectors that cause other diseases
were transported relatively far northward by Hurricane Irene. It is
also not unusual for people trying to recover from events such as a
hurricane to be more focused on their own issues than on sick deer.

We certainly hope the EHD season is a short one. Typically, frost
tends to decrease the vectors and the disease stops.

North Carolina may be found on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive
map at http://healthmap.org/r/1s-V - Mod.TG]
